description.p:
In another embodiment, there is a method of forming a perforation on a substrate comprising:


generating a plurality of beamlets from a laser beam;

directing said plurality of beamlets to a scanner;

operating said scanner to simultaneously contact said plurality of beamlets with said substrate at a plurality of different locations on a substrate within a first dimension and in a second dimension that is orthogonal to said first dimension; and

forming a plurality of perforations on said substrate using said operating step.

claim.claim-text:
The perforation system (500) of claim 1, wherein said laser system (510) further comprises:
a beam expander (540) that is located between said laser (520) and said optical beamlet generator (560;590) proceeding along said optical path;
a beam homogenizer (550) that is located between said beam expander (540) and said optical beamlet generator (560;590) proceeding along said optical path;
wherein said optical beamlet generator is located between said beam homogenizer (550) and said scanner (580) proceeding along said optical path.

A method of forming a perforation (12) on a substrate (20), comprising:
generating a plurality of beamlets (570) from a laser beam (530);
directing said plurality of beamlets (570) to a scanner (580);
operating said scanner (580) to simultaneously contact said plurality of beamlets (570) with said substrate (20) at a plurality of different locations on said substrate (20) within a first dimension and in a second dimension that is orthogonal to said first dimension; and
forming a plurality of perforations (12) on said substrate (20) using said operating step.
